ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.98                 Enzyme
NAME        chlorogenate---glucarate O-hydroxycinnamoyltransferase;
            chlorogenate:glucarate caffeoyltransferase;
            chlorogenic acid:glucaric acid O-caffeoyltransferase;
            chlorogenate:glucarate caffeoyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     chlorogenate:glucarate O-(hydroxycinnamoyl)transferase
REACTION    chlorogenate + glucarate = quinate + 2-O-caffeoylglucarate [RN:R02998]
ALL_REAC    R02998
SUBSTRATE   chlorogenate [CPD:C00852];
            glucarate [CPD:C00818]
PRODUCT     quinate [CPD:C00296];
            2-O-caffeoylglucarate [CPD:C03062]
COMMENT     Galactarate can act as acceptor, more slowly. Involved with EC 2.3.1.99 quinate O-hydroxycinnamoyltransferase in the formation of caffeoylglucarate in tomato.
HISTORY     EC 2.3.1.98 created 1989, modified 1990
